item.title: Coalition ‘deserves uppercut’: Littleproud
item.description: A senior federal Nationals MP admits the coalition "deserves an uppercut" for the self-indulgent conduct of its politicians in the race for Eden-Monaro preselection.

item.title: Iran’s 5.1 quake kills two, injures 22
item.description: Two people died and 22 were injured when they fled their homes in panic during an earthquake of magnitude 5.1 that struck northern Iran early on Friday, state media said.

item.title: AMP shareholders furious over exec pay
item.description: AMP shareholders, denied dividends for 2019, have served a first `strike' on the hefty pay packets of the beleaguered financial giant's executives.

item.title: Million-dollar firewood theft in Tasmania
item.description: Nineteen people in Tasmania are facing hundreds of charges for allegedly stealing about $1 million worth of firewood from reserve areas.

item.title: British rapper Ty dies from virus aged 47
item.description: British rapper Ty has died aged 47 after contracting coronavirus, according to a fundraising page set up to support him.

item.title: Pacific island nations receive rapid tests
item.description: Australia has partnered with international allies to provide rapid coronavirus testing kits to vulnerable Pacific island nations.

item.title: India factory gas leak kills at least 11
item.description: A gas leak at a chemical factory owned by a South Korean company in southern India has left at least 11 people dead and about 1000 struggling to breathe.

item.title: Melbourne film festival goes online
item.description: The Melbourne International Film Festival was cancelled due to coronavirus, but movie buffs can still get a dose of cinema magic in 2020.

item.title: Parents fly to see new surrogate children
item.description: Australian parents are being allowed to travel overseas to see the birth of their surrogate babies during the country's coronavirus lockdown.

item.title: Indonesia tasks China over burials at sea
item.description: Indonesia has summoned China's ambassador to clarify the deaths of four Indonesian crew from two Chinese-flagged vessels, Indonesia's foreign ministry says, after rights groups alleged the crew were mistreated and exploited.
